Title: DRONEWATCH
Credit: Written by
Author: Commander Tom / Claude Code (claude-sonnet-4-6)
Draft date: 2026-06-23
Contact: IDF Defense Innovation Unit

===

FADE IN:

EXT. OPEN BATTLEFIELD - NIGHT

A desolate landscape. Smoke in the distance. Three IDF SOLDIERS move carefully across open ground, scanning the horizon.

SUPER: "THE THREAT"

The soldiers crouch. One raises his rifle. Another checks his radio. They are exposed — no cover for 200 meters in any direction.

SUPER: "FIBER OPTIC DRONES"
SUPER: "Silent. Precise. Lethal."

A small FIBER OPTIC DRONE appears from the darkness, moving fast and low. No warning. No sound. The soldiers do not see it coming.

The drone accelerates toward the soldiers.

CUT TO:

EXT. BATTLEFIELD - CONTINUOUS

The drone closes in. The soldiers scramble — too late, too exposed.

SUPER: "NO WARNING. NO TIME."

SMASH CUT TO BLACK.

===

INT./EXT. DETECTION ZONE - CONTINUOUS

A digital RADAR DISPLAY pulses to life. Concentric rings expand outward from a central point: 100m... 200m... 400m... 500m.

SUPER: "DRONEWATCH"
SUPER: "Ground-Based Drone Early Warning System"

The drone enters the 500-meter detection radius. The system reacts instantly.

A SIREN WAIL cuts through the air.

SUPER: "DETECTION RANGE: 400–500 METERS"
SUPER: "ALERT TIME: UNDER 3 SECONDS"

On a tactical display, SOLDIER ICONS begin moving — away from open ground, toward ARMORED VEHICLE icons and FORTIFIED BUILDING icons.

SUPER: "ACOUSTIC + MOTION DETECTION"
SUPER: "Soldiers alerted. Soldiers moving. Soldiers safe."

===

EXT. OPEN BATTLEFIELD - MOMENTS LATER

The battlefield is empty. Silent. No soldiers visible.

The DRONE arrives at the coordinates — and finds nothing.

It veers — and strikes a CONCRETE WALL.

A dull EXPLOSION. Smoke. But no casualties.

SUPER: "EMPTY BATTLEFIELD"
SUPER: "DRONE: NEUTRALIZED"

WIDE SHOT: Soldiers visible through the windows of armored vehicles and reinforced positions. Safe. Alert. Alive.

SUPER: "DRONEWATCH"
SUPER: "BECAUSE EVERY SECOND COUNTS."

FADE TO BLACK.

TITLE CARD: "DRONEWATCH — Protecting Those Who Protect Us"

FADE OUT.
